1
00:00:18,980 --> 00:00:24,420
♪It's a sordid story that you've made♪

2
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:32,700
♪Up to fill my mind with doubts and pain♪

3
00:00:34,780 --> 00:00:40,220
♪Blood I shed, and tears I wept,
are you satisfied?♪

4
00:00:40,220 --> 00:00:42,540
♪Enjoying what's mine♪

5
00:00:42,540 --> 00:00:49,500
♪Have you found a way
to bury guilt and shame♪

6
00:00:50,540 --> 00:00:55,020
♪I'm coming back to life♪

7
00:00:55,020 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Through the seven gates of death♪

8
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:02,820
♪I'm coming back survived♪

9
00:01:02,820 --> 00:01:06,580
♪Feeling great to see you fall♪

10
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:10,820
♪I'm taking back what's mine♪

11
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:15,340
♪Bringing horror to the battlefield♪

12
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:19,060
♪Lay it to waste♪

13
00:01:19,060 --> 00:01:22,940
♪Til the day my kingdom is reclaimed♪

14
00:01:38,260 --> 00:01:42,540
=Her Blaze=

15
00:01:43,260 --> 00:01:45,780
=Episode 26=

16
00:01:58,879 --> 00:02:01,319
- Welcome!
- Warm welcome!

17
00:02:01,799 --> 00:02:05,439
- Welcome!
- Warm welcome!

18
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,680
- Welcome!
- Warm welcome!

19
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:10,520
- Welcome!
- Warm welcome!

20
00:02:10,599 --> 00:02:13,199
- Welcome!
- Warm welcome!

21
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:16,400
- Welcome!
- Warm welcome!

22
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:18,159
- Welcome!
- Welcome!

23
00:02:18,159 --> 00:02:20,360
- Welcome!
- Warm welcome!

24
00:02:20,479 --> 00:02:23,479
- Welcome!
- Warm welcome!

25
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:26,639
You're back.

26
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:28,900
It's good to have you back.

27
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:33,000
- Welcome!
- Warm welcome!

28
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:35,120
Welcome, welcome.

29
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,080
Ms. Rao.

30
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,080
Ms. Rao.

31
00:03:05,039 --> 00:03:06,000
Starting today,

32
00:03:06,650 --> 00:03:08,090
I am officially returning to my post.

33
00:03:08,759 --> 00:03:11,319
- Welcome back!
- Welcome back!

34
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:21,319
I have something to announce.

35
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Effective immediately,

36
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,000
the company is halting all projects

37
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:25,890
in Dept 2 and Dept 3,

38
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,070
including the green building
materials company acquisition

39
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:30,520
and the Snack Street Renewal Plan.

40
00:03:32,439 --> 00:03:33,240
Why?

41
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:37,039
The most important thing
for Lysen right now

42
00:03:37,039 --> 00:03:39,350
is the tripartite cooperation
between Bosi, Baiye, and ourselves,

43
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,590
as well as the financing conference.

44
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:43,360
But Ms. Rao, ever since
you first joined the company,

45
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:45,319
you were the one who led everyone
to work on these projects.

46
00:03:45,319 --> 00:03:46,560
After all that hard work we put in...

47
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,400
The beginning was the beginning.

48
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,479
Now is now.

49
00:03:49,759 --> 00:03:51,400
I've made myself very clear.

50
00:03:52,599 --> 00:03:55,199
Please comply
with the company's arrangements.

51
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,639
And what if I don't agree?

52
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,199
Mr. Yu,

53
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:10,039
live to fight another day.

54
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:23,680
Ms. Ren, if anyone wants to resign,
process their paperwork.

55
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:33,959
Are you and Jiang Dongchao
out of your minds?

56
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,360
Come on in.

57
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,360
Mr. Jiang.

58
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:07,830
Ms. Rao has already halted
all projects in Dept 2 and Dept 3.

59
00:05:08,519 --> 00:05:09,519
The staff's reaction

60
00:05:10,150 --> 00:05:11,040
has been quite intense.

61
00:05:14,319 --> 00:05:15,680
What was Yu Peidong's reaction?

62
00:05:15,839 --> 00:05:16,879
He's very angry.

63
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,190
It's only right that he's angry.

64
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:24,959
Then,

65
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,319
what about you?

66
00:05:31,839 --> 00:05:33,240
I remember you once said

67
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:34,519
that at Lysen,

68
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,920
if we want to go far,

69
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:37,319
we can't have any weaknesses.

70
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:38,759
Don't worry.

71
00:05:39,319 --> 00:05:41,360
I understand the principle.

72
00:05:45,959 --> 00:05:46,759
Get back to work.

73
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,000
You're leaving too?

74
00:06:04,959 --> 00:06:06,199
So, you've decided to stay?

75
00:06:08,279 --> 00:06:09,319
Why should I leave?

76
00:06:09,879 --> 00:06:11,600
I worked so hard to get into Lysen.

77
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:13,879
Besides,

78
00:06:14,279 --> 00:06:15,680
I think what Ms. Rao is doing

79
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,040
is perfectly fine.

80
00:06:19,279 --> 00:06:20,160
I wish you success.

81
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:30,500
(Lysen Group)

82
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,199
Tian Tian, do you really plan on leaving?

83
00:06:53,199 --> 00:06:54,720
Don't misunderstand me, Yuci.

84
00:06:55,639 --> 00:06:56,959
I don't mean to blame you.

85
00:06:58,680 --> 00:06:59,480
Actually,

86
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:02,759
I can understand you.

87
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,639
When I first came to Lysen,

88
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:08,680
you were the one who saved me
at the most critical moment.

89
00:07:09,959 --> 00:07:10,839
You from back then

90
00:07:10,839 --> 00:07:11,720
were afraid of nothing.

91
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:12,800
You were fearless.

92
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,800
Well, make yourself capable,

93
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,800
make yourself strong.

94
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:19,600
Believe in yourself
that you can defeat those

95
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,720
who don't follow the rules

96
00:07:20,879 --> 00:07:22,199
and those who are unkind.

97
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:25,360
Let them know
what a backlash feels like.

98
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,279
Now you look like

99
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,480
you've become even stronger.

100
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,079
But in your eyes,

101
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:37,319
I can sense a trace of fear.

102
00:07:41,759 --> 00:07:42,959
You don't have to answer me.

103
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,879
I think I can sense why.

104
00:07:47,519 --> 00:07:48,600
It's because you care.

105
00:07:49,759 --> 00:07:50,920
You care about us.

106
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,279
But I'm just a little sad

107
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,120
that you still choose not to trust us

108
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:00,199
and choose to bear

109
00:08:00,199 --> 00:08:01,439
all of this alone.

110
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:07,399
So,

111
00:08:08,399 --> 00:08:09,839
since I can't be of any help,

112
00:08:11,439 --> 00:08:13,040
I'll take my leave for now.

113
00:08:14,279 --> 00:08:15,079
But

114
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:18,120
I still believe in the person
you were then,

115
00:08:18,759 --> 00:08:20,319
and I believe in you now.

116
00:08:21,279 --> 00:08:23,720
Even though I don't know
what you plan to do next,

117
00:08:24,399 --> 00:08:26,199
I'm certain you haven't changed.

118
00:08:27,399 --> 00:08:29,040
You're still the same Yuci.

119
00:08:30,519 --> 00:08:32,159
You burst into all of our lives

120
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:33,559
like a ray of light,

121
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,399
telling us that this world

122
00:08:35,399 --> 00:08:37,240
isn't what others see.

123
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,039
Thank you.

124
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:43,279
We still have a bit of our ideals left.

125
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,120
To humanity.

126
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:46,170
- To humanity!
- To humanity!

127
00:08:46,919 --> 00:08:47,720
Yuci,

128
00:08:49,799 --> 00:08:50,720
don't be afraid.

129
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:52,559
Don't be scared.

130
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,480
As long as you've made up your mind,

131
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:56,519
whenever you need us,
we will always be here.

132
00:08:57,679 --> 00:08:59,320
But you must remember

133
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:01,080
what you once told me.

134
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,559
Stay true to your original

135
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,279
and authentic self.

136
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,639
Only then will they be afraid.

137
00:09:58,799 --> 00:10:00,799
I can't believe you
dared to ask me here.

138
00:10:03,879 --> 00:10:05,000
Let's talk.

139
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:06,879
Talk about what?

140
00:10:07,410 --> 00:10:08,960
I only want you to pay with your life.

141
00:10:30,639 --> 00:10:33,279
I don't think your mother
would want to see you like this.

142
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,840
You have no right to mention Bai Xia!

143
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:41,639
She is dead,

144
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:43,200
and it's all your fault!

145
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:46,600
You should know very well

146
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:49,679
that this whole situation

147
00:10:49,679 --> 00:10:51,399
was created by you.

148
00:10:52,759 --> 00:10:54,399
Not only did you ruin your mother,

149
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:56,960
but years ago,

150
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:59,000
your selfishness and cruelty

151
00:11:00,519 --> 00:11:01,960
also killed Professor Han.

152
00:11:03,039 --> 00:11:04,360
Do you still remember him?

153
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:18,660
(Five years ago)

154
00:11:20,340 --> 00:11:23,700
(Presenter: Rao Yuci)

155
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:31,020
(Supervisor: Han Dehai.
Title: Professor)

156
00:11:31,020 --> 00:11:34,870
(Find a way to get Professor Han
to accept my postgrad recommendation)

157
00:11:34,871 --> 00:11:39,820
(If he refuses, make him
leave and lose his professorship)

158
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:40,639
That's her.

159
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:42,799
I heard Professor Han
thinks highly of her.

160
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,290
He even gave
the recommendation spot to her.

161
00:11:44,399 --> 00:11:45,200
Why?

162
00:11:45,380 --> 00:11:48,519
Throughout the four years of university,
she ranked first in every major exam.

163
00:11:48,519 --> 00:11:50,190
If it were you,
who would you give it to?

164
00:11:55,039 --> 00:11:57,440
Professor Han, this is
the book you recommended,

165
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,559
"Macroeconomics".

166
00:11:58,600 --> 00:11:59,600
I've finished reading it.

167
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,480
I've included my notes inside.

168
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:04,080
The blue marks

169
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,720
are where I still have questions.

170
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,720
The green marks are the parts

171
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:09,390
I thought were
exceptionally well-written.

172
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:11,000
Well organized.

173
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:15,080
Professor Han,

174
00:12:15,759 --> 00:12:17,159
regarding what I mentioned

175
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,919
about applying to be
your graduate student,

176
00:12:19,279 --> 00:12:20,679
what do you think?

177
00:12:28,159 --> 00:12:28,960
Liangliang,

178
00:12:30,759 --> 00:12:32,879
doing research
might not be suitable for you.

179
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:35,519
Let's look at things practically.

180
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,120
I think

181
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,639
what you should consider most right now

182
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,799
is your upcoming employment.

183
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:43,390
I can recommend
a state-owned enterprise to you.

184
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,320
Their benefits are quite good.

185
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:46,759
As soon as you start,

186
00:12:47,039 --> 00:12:48,279
you'll receive a high salary.

187
00:12:49,159 --> 00:12:49,960
I believe this is

188
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,399
the most suitable path for you.

189
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:53,360
My grades are good enough.

190
00:12:53,399 --> 00:12:55,039
Why can't I do research?

191
00:12:58,039 --> 00:13:00,600
Financial mathematics
is a theoretical science.

192
00:13:00,919 --> 00:13:03,080
It requires total devotion.

193
00:13:03,639 --> 00:13:05,759
Given your current family situation,

194
00:13:06,159 --> 00:13:07,440
can it support you

195
00:13:07,759 --> 00:13:09,519
on the path

196
00:13:09,919 --> 00:13:10,879
of theoretical research?

197
00:13:12,159 --> 00:13:13,360
What do you mean?

198
00:13:14,039 --> 00:13:14,840
I'm sorry.

199
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:17,080
Maybe I was a bit too direct.

200
00:13:17,919 --> 00:13:19,080
However, your counselor

201
00:13:19,799 --> 00:13:20,559
has briefed me

202
00:13:20,559 --> 00:13:21,799
on your family situation.

203
00:13:22,399 --> 00:13:23,720
Your father has suffered a stroke.

204
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:26,960
I think you should find a job
as soon as possible

205
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:29,000
to share the family's burden.

206
00:13:29,090 --> 00:13:30,240
Besides, after starting work,

207
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:32,500
you can still pursue
a part-time master's degree.

208
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:34,159
That is an option.

209
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:39,320
Thank you, Professor Han.

210
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,519
Hello, Professor Han?

211
00:14:00,639 --> 00:14:01,799
Are you on campus?

212
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:05,200
I'll come to see you a bit later.

213
00:14:07,039 --> 00:14:07,879
See you later.

214
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:17,919
Liangliang.

215
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:20,159
They say Professor Han resigned

216
00:14:20,159 --> 00:14:21,600
because someone reported him.

217
00:14:22,559 --> 00:14:23,480
Reported what?

218
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:25,919
You know, those things
between men and women.

219
00:14:27,039 --> 00:14:29,039
The whole school
is talking about it now, right?

220
00:14:30,639 --> 00:14:32,879
I was already guaranteed
to be his graduate student.

221
00:14:33,279 --> 00:14:34,600
Then, this suddenly happened.

222
00:14:35,279 --> 00:14:36,320
I thought Professor Han

223
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,600
was such a good person.

224
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:38,879
What do you think?

225
00:14:39,639 --> 00:14:40,960
Do you think it's true?

226
00:14:44,679 --> 00:14:46,360
Everyone has another side.

227
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:48,039
Professor Han is no exception.

228
00:14:51,759 --> 00:14:52,559
Let's go.

229
00:15:23,559 --> 00:15:24,919
Alright, let's stop our review

230
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:26,480
of what we learned before.

231
00:15:26,679 --> 00:15:29,600
Now, we'll discuss a new concept.

232
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:31,480
And that is mapping.

233
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:33,759
Mapping.

234
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,000
You know this...

235
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:37,039
Professor Han.

236
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:39,320
Professor Han!

237
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:40,639
Here,

238
00:15:40,799 --> 00:15:43,120
we first need to understand

239
00:15:43,120 --> 00:15:44,440
the definition of mapping.

240
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:46,159
Suppose,

241
00:15:46,919 --> 00:15:48,480
X and Y

242
00:15:49,559 --> 00:15:51,279
are two non-empty sets.

243
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:53,559
Suppose there exists a rule, F.

244
00:15:54,639 --> 00:15:55,559
For every element, X,

245
00:15:55,559 --> 00:15:57,159
within X,

246
00:15:57,639 --> 00:15:59,120
according to this rule,

247
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:00,639
then in...

248
00:16:00,639 --> 00:16:01,440
Professor Han.

249
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:02,960
Yuci.

250
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:04,480
It's been a while.

251
00:16:07,679 --> 00:16:09,440
As you can see, it's a mess in here.

252
00:16:11,039 --> 00:16:12,519
Why are you standing? Have a seat.

253
00:16:15,559 --> 00:16:16,840
Are you here to borrow a book?

254
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:20,080
Han,

255
00:16:21,039 --> 00:16:22,639
I've got the eggs I bought for you.

256
00:16:23,799 --> 00:16:25,039
You have a guest?

257
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:27,960
My student, Rao Yuci.

258
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,879
This young lady is so pretty.

259
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:33,679
Thank you, ma'am.

260
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:34,950
Alright, I'll let you get back to it.

261
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:36,879
Remember to put
these eggs in the fridge.

262
00:16:37,799 --> 00:16:38,639
Give them to me.

263
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:42,600
Miss, talk some sense into him.

264
00:16:42,879 --> 00:16:44,799
He refuses to close his door every day.

265
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:46,120
Okay, ma'am.

266
00:16:49,100 --> 00:16:49,840
Talk to him, okay?

267
00:17:03,879 --> 00:17:04,759
Professor Han,

268
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:08,279
why don't you close the door?

269
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:09,119
Don't close it.

270
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:10,680
Don't close the door.

271
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,720
If it's closed, I can't explain myself.

272
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:13,839
Never close it.

273
00:17:24,039 --> 00:17:25,240
Yuci, thank you.

274
00:17:26,079 --> 00:17:27,480
You're welcome, Professor Han.

275
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:28,759
Miss,

276
00:17:28,839 --> 00:17:29,759
come out for a moment.

277
00:17:30,279 --> 00:17:31,279
What is it, ma'am?

278
00:17:31,519 --> 00:17:33,119
Miss, let me ask you.

279
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:34,240
How old are you?

280
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:35,599
Do you have a boyfriend?

281
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:36,799
Yes.

282
00:17:38,039 --> 00:17:39,079
I thought so.

283
00:17:39,079 --> 00:17:40,279
You're so outstanding.

284
00:17:40,279 --> 00:17:41,079
But

285
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:43,240
(Bai Liangliang)
having a boyfriend doesn't matter.

286
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:45,279
(Bai Liangliang)
As long as you're single, there's a chance.

287
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:48,160
Let me introduce my nephew to you.

288
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:48,759
How about it?

289
00:17:48,759 --> 00:17:49,400
No need, ma'am.

290
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,599
It's fine, just take a look.

291
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:53,119
He has a house and a car.

292
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:54,440
No thanks, ma'am. Thank you.

293
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:56,480
Just take a look, he's handsome.

294
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:58,559
You're young,
so you should get to know each other.

295
00:17:58,580 --> 00:18:02,839
(Bai Liangliang)

296
00:18:02,839 --> 00:18:03,640
Hello,

297
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:05,519
Yuci.

298
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:08,240
I didn't touch you at all.

299
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,160
You're framing me.

300
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:12,640
You are framing me!

301
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,000
Bai Liangliang!

302
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:15,799
You're all in this together!

303
00:18:15,799 --> 00:18:17,279
You are all framing me!

304
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:18,799
Get out, all of you! Get out!

305
00:18:18,799 --> 00:18:20,319
Leave!

306
00:18:20,319 --> 00:18:21,119
Professor Han.

307
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:22,039
Professor Han!

308
00:18:22,039 --> 00:18:23,559
Han, what's wrong with you?

309
00:18:23,559 --> 00:18:24,599
You were fine just now.

310
00:18:24,599 --> 00:18:25,519
I didn't do anything!

311
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,480
No one will believe you!

312
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:29,200
Just leave, quickly!

313
00:18:30,759 --> 00:18:31,920
That was terrifying.

314
00:18:32,039 --> 00:18:33,960
How can this man change so suddenly?

315
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,079
So scary.

316
00:18:35,599 --> 00:18:36,400
Hello?

317
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:38,680
Liangliang.

318
00:19:11,119 --> 00:19:12,039
Professor Han,

319
00:19:13,319 --> 00:19:14,400
are you alright?

320
00:19:15,839 --> 00:19:16,640
Bai Liangliang.

321
00:19:18,079 --> 00:19:19,200
I didn't do anything.

322
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:20,599
I...

323
00:19:21,119 --> 00:19:22,200
I didn't do...

324
00:19:22,240 --> 00:19:23,039
Just leave.

325
00:19:23,039 --> 00:19:23,559
What...

326
00:19:23,559 --> 00:19:24,559
What are you doing here?

327
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:26,480
Haven't you ruined me enough?

328
00:19:32,759 --> 00:19:33,599
Professor Han.

329
00:19:36,319 --> 00:19:37,160
Professor Han.

330
00:19:43,359 --> 00:19:46,039
Miss, so it's you.

331
00:19:46,039 --> 00:19:46,839
Ma'am,

332
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:48,359
is Professor Han not home?

333
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:50,640
Miss,

334
00:19:50,640 --> 00:19:51,839
you probably don't know yet.

335
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:54,519
The night before last,
Professor Han had a sudden heart attack.

336
00:19:54,519 --> 00:19:56,039
He collapsed in front of his desk

337
00:19:56,559 --> 00:19:57,559
and passed away.

338
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:19,480
It wasn't me.

339
00:20:20,799 --> 00:20:21,599
It was you.

340
00:20:23,039 --> 00:20:24,920
You were the one who kept fighting me,

341
00:20:25,559 --> 00:20:27,279
and you even dragged Bai Xia into this.

342
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:29,759
You caused all of this.

343
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:32,400
But it's useless.

344
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:33,759
Rao Yuci,

345
00:20:34,799 --> 00:20:36,559
Jiang Dongchao will never believe you.

346
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:39,400
I have Bai Qingyu backing me up.

347
00:20:40,119 --> 00:20:41,599
Everything you've planned

348
00:20:41,599 --> 00:20:42,799
will fail.

349
00:20:42,799 --> 00:20:44,240
You can't defeat me.

350
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:46,680
Rao Yuci, remember this.

351
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:47,759
This matter

352
00:20:47,759 --> 00:20:49,599
won't end so easily.

353
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:53,079
Bai Liangliang,

354
00:20:53,079 --> 00:20:54,519
are you going to keep doing this?

355
00:20:56,839 --> 00:20:58,599
When will you be able

356
00:20:58,599 --> 00:20:59,839
to see your own heart clearly?

357
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:05,839
You possessed
the most precious thing in the world.

358
00:21:07,079 --> 00:21:08,119
But you only believe in

359
00:21:08,119 --> 00:21:09,680
what you've imagined.

360
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:14,519
Do you know what you've missed out on?

361
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,920
These are Ms. Bai Xia's belongings.

362
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:21,319
We have already organized everything.

363
00:21:21,319 --> 00:21:23,039
Please check and sign for them.

364
00:21:30,540 --> 00:21:36,480
♪It's a sordid story that you've made♪

365
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:37,319
Take a look.

366
00:21:37,319 --> 00:21:38,660
(Year 1999)

367
00:21:38,660 --> 00:21:44,420
♪Up to fill my mind
with doubts and pain♪

368
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:49,759
(This year)

369
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:52,000
(was a hard year.)

370
00:21:53,519 --> 00:21:55,200
(I finally found her.)

371
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:59,079
(Today, I brought her back home.)

372
00:21:59,319 --> 00:22:00,200
Look, is it pretty?

373
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,519
I don't want it! I want to find my dad!

374
00:22:01,519 --> 00:22:02,160
Liangliang.

375
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:05,799
I want to find my dad!

376
00:22:08,559 --> 00:22:09,640
(But the child)

377
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:12,440
(no longer recognizes me.)

378
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:14,880
(The child always asks me,)

379
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:17,240
("Where did Dad go?")

380
00:22:19,599 --> 00:22:21,119
(How can I tell her)

381
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:24,480
(that her father is a gambler?)

382
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:28,200
(I was originally the one who was hurt,)

383
00:22:29,799 --> 00:22:30,680
(but why)

384
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:32,160
(should I pass the pain)

385
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:35,200
(I suffered onto my child?)

386
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:37,039
(Bai Xia,)

387
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:39,319
(just hang in there a bit longer.)

388
00:22:39,799 --> 00:22:41,440
(Maybe after some time,)

389
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:43,079
(she will be fine.)

390
00:22:43,759 --> 00:22:45,440
(You are always her mother,)

391
00:22:46,799 --> 00:22:49,079
(and she is always your child.)

392
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:54,620
♪I'm coming back untamed♪

393
00:22:58,519 --> 00:23:00,720
(Today, I learned how
to make salted duck.)

394
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:03,000
(In the future,)

395
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:04,920
(I can use this skill)

396
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:06,039
(to support her.)

397
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:08,640
Liangliang, look.

398
00:23:08,799 --> 00:23:10,400
I saved a duck leg for you.

399
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:18,960
A bit higher.

400
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:19,599
Okay.

401
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:20,839
One, two, three.

402
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:21,960
Up!

403
00:23:23,119 --> 00:23:23,920
Up we go!

404
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:27,279
(A child always needs a father.)

405
00:23:28,079 --> 00:23:30,000
(A mother cannot replace that.)

406
00:23:30,759 --> 00:23:31,880
(How could I not)

407
00:23:31,880 --> 00:23:33,119
(understand this truth?)

408
00:23:35,440 --> 00:23:36,240
(That day,)

409
00:23:37,119 --> 00:23:39,000
(I took Liangliang to meet him.)

410
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,880
This is our new home.

411
00:23:41,319 --> 00:23:42,599
Quick, say hello.

412
00:23:46,079 --> 00:23:47,400
(I don't actually love him.)

413
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:50,279
(I only chose to be with him)

414
00:23:50,279 --> 00:23:52,000
(to fulfill Liangliang's wish)

415
00:23:52,119 --> 00:23:53,960
(of having a father.)

416
00:23:55,839 --> 00:23:57,039
(But I found)

417
00:23:58,279 --> 00:24:00,559
(that Liangliang
didn't seem very happy.)

418
00:24:01,039 --> 00:24:02,680
Liangliang, look.

419
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:04,839
He bought this as a gift for you.

420
00:24:05,519 --> 00:24:06,440
(I know)

421
00:24:07,319 --> 00:24:08,160
(that this man)

422
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:10,160
(might not be the father
Liangliang had in mind.)

423
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,839
Look at all this candy. Do you like it?

424
00:24:11,839 --> 00:24:14,119
(Perhaps time will change everything.)

425
00:24:18,559 --> 00:24:20,079
Take this to him.

426
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:23,759
Tell him you bought it for him
with your saved pocket money.

427
00:24:24,460 --> 00:24:28,540
♪I'm coming back survived♪

428
00:24:28,540 --> 00:24:32,700
♪Feeling great to see you fall♪

429
00:24:32,700 --> 00:24:36,700
♪I'm taking back what's mine♪

430
00:24:39,839 --> 00:24:41,599
(That day at the rehabilitation center,)

431
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:43,880
(I heard everyone)

432
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:45,400
(discussing their wills.)

433
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:48,160
(I haven't been a successful mother.)

434
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:51,720
(I have nothing)

435
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:53,400
(to leave for Liangliang.)

436
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,880
(The child doesn't even)

437
00:24:56,559 --> 00:24:59,640
(want to look at me anymore.)

438
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,279
(If the time really comes)

439
00:25:02,519 --> 00:25:04,480
(when our bond
as mother and daughter ends,)

440
00:25:06,359 --> 00:25:07,160
(please)

441
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:11,480
(make sure to say a proper goodbye
to Liangliang.)

442
00:25:13,799 --> 00:25:15,359
I also hope

443
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:18,839
that you can live a good life.

444
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:46,720
These letters...

445
00:25:48,319 --> 00:25:50,359
I won't accept a single word of them.

446
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:03,799
Why did you have to tear up

447
00:26:03,799 --> 00:26:04,640
these letters?

448
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:08,279
These are all

449
00:26:08,279 --> 00:26:09,640
the love your mother gave you.

450
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:14,039
What kind of mother is Bai Xia?

451
00:26:15,759 --> 00:26:17,680
She always wanted me to settle for less.

452
00:26:18,039 --> 00:26:19,359
Why should I just accept my fate?

453
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:23,559
She's already gone.

454
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:27,599
But while she lived in this world,

455
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:31,839
she gave all her sincerity

456
00:26:31,839 --> 00:26:33,000
and love to you.

457
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:36,799
If she really loved me,

458
00:26:38,920 --> 00:26:40,839
she wouldn't have
caused me so much pain,

459
00:26:41,010 --> 00:26:43,319
and she certainly shouldn't
have helped you deal with me.

460
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:45,759
While I was being beaten, one thought

461
00:26:45,759 --> 00:26:47,720
kept flashing through my mind.

462
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:51,400
Physical harm

463
00:26:52,720 --> 00:26:53,960
is actually nothing.

464
00:26:55,839 --> 00:26:56,680
Sometimes,

465
00:26:58,799 --> 00:26:59,839
a regret

466
00:27:04,039 --> 00:27:05,880
or a departure without a goodbye

467
00:27:08,279 --> 00:27:10,039
is what can destroy a person.

468
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:15,440
Bai Liangliang,

469
00:27:20,079 --> 00:27:21,119
when you realize

470
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:23,599
everything you believed in

471
00:27:23,599 --> 00:27:24,720
was a lie...

472
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:31,039
You misunderstood the person

473
00:27:32,160 --> 00:27:33,240
you should have cared about

474
00:27:35,519 --> 00:27:37,440
and hurt those

475
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:39,559
you never should have hurt.

476
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:45,559
You've let down every sincere heart.

477
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:52,000
I hope that one day,

478
00:27:54,519 --> 00:27:56,039
you will have a sudden realization,

479
00:27:58,200 --> 00:27:59,079
and you will be able

480
00:27:59,079 --> 00:28:00,400
to see your own heart clearly.

481
00:28:02,880 --> 00:28:03,880
But I'm afraid

482
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:07,279
that when that day comes,

483
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:12,160
all those people will already be gone.

484
00:28:19,039 --> 00:28:19,839
For me,

485
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,359
for your mother,

486
00:28:24,039 --> 00:28:25,119
and for everyone you've

487
00:28:25,119 --> 00:28:26,680
ever hurt,

488
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:30,519
just live in the darkness alone

489
00:28:32,319 --> 00:28:33,400
for the rest of your life.

490
00:28:57,079 --> 00:28:58,279
How come it's you?

491
00:29:17,359 --> 00:29:18,160
Mom,

492
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:20,440
was I wrong?

493
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:37,079
I wasn't wrong.

494
00:29:47,759 --> 00:29:48,559
Dongchao,

495
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:50,799
I've already
settled things with Yang Jinwan.

496
00:29:51,119 --> 00:29:52,119
There's no time to lose.

497
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:53,400
You can prepare

498
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,160
to convene the financing conference

499
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:56,319
and formally announce

500
00:29:56,319 --> 00:29:57,799
our tripartite cooperation.

501
00:29:57,839 --> 00:29:59,359
At that time, Yang Jinwan and I

502
00:29:59,359 --> 00:30:00,559
will be present.

503
00:30:00,760 --> 00:30:02,039
Thank you for your help, Ms. Bai.

504
00:30:02,720 --> 00:30:04,079
It's a good idea.

505
00:30:04,599 --> 00:30:07,000
Being able to formally announce it
is half the battle.

506
00:30:07,359 --> 00:30:09,000
We just need to clarify

507
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:10,359
the distribution of interests.

508
00:30:10,559 --> 00:30:12,660
Let's arrange to meet him again
as soon as possible.

509
00:30:12,920 --> 00:30:13,720
Understood.

510
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:20,720
Come on in.

511
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:22,799
Mr. Jiang.

512
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:24,519
I'm going to announce

513
00:30:24,519 --> 00:30:26,319
the strategic cooperation

514
00:30:26,319 --> 00:30:27,599
between Lysen, Bosi, and Baiye.

515
00:30:28,519 --> 00:30:29,920
Invite the board members

516
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,359
and the higher-ups of the company.

517
00:30:33,519 --> 00:30:35,000
Go and draft a meeting agenda.

518
00:30:35,759 --> 00:30:36,839
This is the top priority

519
00:30:36,839 --> 00:30:37,839
of our recent work.

520
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:39,880
Don't bother me

521
00:30:40,279 --> 00:30:41,119
with anything else.

522
00:30:42,319 --> 00:30:43,279
Understood, Mr. Jiang.

523
00:31:00,759 --> 00:31:01,400
I still remember

524
00:31:01,400 --> 00:31:02,480
when I first came to Lysen

525
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:04,720
after I graduated,

526
00:31:06,839 --> 00:31:09,039
you'd drag me to
this observation deck every few days.

527
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:12,440
You told me

528
00:31:14,279 --> 00:31:15,920
human nature is too complicated

529
00:31:16,519 --> 00:31:18,039
and society is too complicated.

530
00:31:20,039 --> 00:31:20,839
It seems

531
00:31:21,839 --> 00:31:23,160
that at some point,

532
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:25,160
it became you comforting me instead.

533
00:31:26,200 --> 00:31:28,240
Women are just more mature than men.

534
00:31:32,359 --> 00:31:33,240
Later on, we had

535
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:34,680
a huge fight here and broke up.

536
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:37,559
I never came back up here again.

537
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:47,200
Peidong.

538
00:31:52,839 --> 00:31:53,839
Don't leave, okay?

539
00:31:58,039 --> 00:31:58,799
What are you doing?

540
00:31:58,799 --> 00:31:59,640
We're not kids anymore.

541
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:00,990
Don't let people see us like this.

542
00:32:02,100 --> 00:32:04,000
I won't jump into
the Huangpu River that easily.

543
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:04,799
Rest assured.

544
00:32:12,079 --> 00:32:13,599
On the contrary, I feel that Lysen

545
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:18,190
is increasingly lacking the responsibility
of a grand enterprise.

546
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:19,880
It's turned into

547
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:21,400
an intrigue-filled colosseum.

548
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:23,790
Take the green building
materials companies.

549
00:32:25,759 --> 00:32:27,079
They only cooperated with us

550
00:32:27,079 --> 00:32:29,160
because of Rao Yuci and me.

551
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:31,790
But as soon as
Jiang Dongchao gave the order,

552
00:32:32,800 --> 00:32:33,960
the production line
that had just resumed

553
00:32:33,960 --> 00:32:35,039
was shut down again.

554
00:32:38,039 --> 00:32:38,920
These small businesses

555
00:32:38,920 --> 00:32:40,200
already have it hard enough.

556
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:42,500
They can't handle
being jerked around like this.

557
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:46,790
Well, we paid out the compensation

558
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:48,480
according to the contract.

559
00:32:48,839 --> 00:32:50,160
Don't you know how aggressive

560
00:32:50,160 --> 00:32:51,160
Lysen's contracts are?

561
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:53,640
The pittance you paid them

562
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:54,960
is nothing more

563
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:56,440
than a drop in the bucket to them.

564
00:33:00,400 --> 00:33:01,680
These are the rules of the game.

565
00:33:03,519 --> 00:33:05,200
I'm not playing this game anymore, okay?

566
00:33:05,599 --> 00:33:06,920
Don't be so impulsive, alright?

567
00:33:07,599 --> 00:33:08,839
You have to trust Rao Yuci.

568
00:33:10,279 --> 00:33:13,319
I believe that she's doing this
for a reason.

569
00:33:14,559 --> 00:33:16,119
As if I don't know her.

570
00:33:17,559 --> 00:33:19,279
She must be planning something big.

571
00:33:19,599 --> 00:33:21,599
Since she doesn't need us right now,

572
00:33:21,839 --> 00:33:24,119
can't we just clear the battlefield for her?

573
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:25,000
I'm leaving.

574
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:26,839
I'll just leave, okay?

575
00:33:42,519 --> 00:33:43,319
I heard...

576
00:33:45,880 --> 00:33:46,599
You want to ask me

577
00:33:46,599 --> 00:33:48,570
about Yu Peidong
and the others resigning, right?

578
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:53,880
Why did you do it?

579
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:56,480
And why

580
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:57,440
the injury on your face?

581
00:33:58,700 --> 00:34:00,799
If you keep this up,
you won't be yourself anymore.

582
00:34:00,799 --> 00:34:01,960
How am I not myself?

583
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:04,359
I was myself then, and I still am now.

584
00:34:04,359 --> 00:34:05,359
Are you yourself now?

585
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:08,480
Everything I'm doing now

586
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:09,960
is my own decision.

587
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:12,440
Sometimes I also wonder

588
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:14,119
why I ended up on this path.

589
00:34:14,960 --> 00:34:15,760
I even wonder

590
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:19,679
why I ever met you.

591
00:34:23,320 --> 00:34:24,960
Maybe everything was predestined.

592
00:34:26,719 --> 00:34:27,970
Just like how it was predestined

593
00:34:29,079 --> 00:34:30,920
that I am Rao Shusheng's daughter.

594
00:34:32,519 --> 00:34:34,280
You've been immersed
in Rao Shusheng's pain

595
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:35,239
for too long.

596
00:34:35,810 --> 00:34:37,760
It's time for you
to say goodbye to all of this.

597
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:45,060
And I have something to tell you

598
00:34:45,360 --> 00:34:46,360
about Rao Shusheng.

599
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:47,440
No need.

600
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:52,519
The thing I wanted to hear before,

601
00:34:53,639 --> 00:34:54,960
the truth about him and me...

602
00:34:56,880 --> 00:34:58,159
I don't need it anymore.

603
00:34:59,500 --> 00:35:00,760
You don't have to say anything.

604
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:02,239
That's great.

605
00:35:03,840 --> 00:35:05,000
It's all in the past now.

606
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:06,390
You don't have to carry it anymore.

607
00:35:10,719 --> 00:35:12,280
You didn't understand what I was saying.

608
00:35:15,039 --> 00:35:16,639
I have made peace with myself.

609
00:35:20,559 --> 00:35:23,239
It's because of that peace
that I see this world clearly now.

610
00:35:24,100 --> 00:35:26,559
Some people just feel
that there must be something in the dark

611
00:35:26,559 --> 00:35:27,880
that is more powerful than light.

612
00:35:28,360 --> 00:35:30,280
Some people simply value interests more.

613
00:35:32,159 --> 00:35:32,960
I think

614
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:36,880
they might be right.

615
00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:37,800
They are wrong.

616
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:41,320
Rao Yuci,

617
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:42,440
that's not how you think.

618
00:35:43,119 --> 00:35:43,800
I've seen you

619
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:45,039
when you were full of sunshine.

620
00:35:47,060 --> 00:35:48,990
When you were helping
the people at Snack Street,

621
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:50,239
you were genuinely happy.

622
00:35:50,639 --> 00:35:51,880
You were truly happy.

623
00:35:57,159 --> 00:35:58,199
(Your smile today)

624
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:00,920
(is a bit different from before.)

625
00:36:09,039 --> 00:36:10,760
You never belonged to the darkness.

626
00:36:12,039 --> 00:36:14,280
Be your true self again, okay?

627
00:36:17,840 --> 00:36:18,840
Chen Mo, I'm sorry.

628
00:36:45,660 --> 00:36:49,420
=Episode 26=
(Backlash)

629
00:36:49,941 --> 00:36:52,381
(All animals in this production
were treated humanely)

630
00:36:52,381 --> 00:36:58,581
♪Take a breath and swallow
the words you couldn't say♪

631
00:36:59,341 --> 00:37:02,541
♪No need to force your heart anymore♪

632
00:37:02,541 --> 00:37:07,061
♪Searching for the season
we once missed♪

633
00:37:07,061 --> 00:37:14,581
♪Leave this place,
though wounded still stay strong♪

634
00:37:14,581 --> 00:37:18,501
♪You must believe
one day the rain will fall♪

635
00:37:18,501 --> 00:37:22,541
♪And wash away the mud
that stains your soul♪

636
00:37:22,541 --> 00:37:26,061
♪Find your freedom in the wild♪

637
00:37:26,061 --> 00:37:30,021
♪Take your stride and move ahead♪

638
00:37:30,021 --> 00:37:34,181
♪I will stay behind
and wait for your eyes♪

639
00:37:34,181 --> 00:37:38,381
♪To rebuild
the same flesh and soul again♪

640
00:37:38,381 --> 00:37:42,181
♪Wander freely through the thorns♪

641
00:37:42,181 --> 00:37:46,261
♪Keep walking through the light♪

642
00:37:46,261 --> 00:37:50,461
♪Fate is absurd, don't stop for anyone♪

643
00:37:50,461 --> 00:37:56,781
♪What you dare to lose
will one day be your own♪

644
00:38:13,901 --> 00:38:20,541
♪I'm sorry, I still owe you these words♪

645
00:38:20,541 --> 00:38:24,381
♪An apology that came too late♪

646
00:38:24,381 --> 00:38:29,021
♪Yet it's also the path
that saves my soul♪

647
00:38:29,101 --> 00:38:36,501
♪When the cold wind
passes it takes the past away♪

648
00:38:36,501 --> 00:38:40,581
♪You must believe and stand unwavering♪

649
00:38:40,581 --> 00:38:44,661
♪There will be hands
to pull you from the deep♪

650
00:38:44,661 --> 00:38:48,661
♪Find your freedom in the silence♪

651
00:38:48,661 --> 00:38:52,421
♪Let your wounds be mended♪

652
00:38:52,421 --> 00:38:56,621
♪Gray is not the past
and pain is not a shame♪

653
00:38:56,621 --> 00:39:00,781
♪Sometimes the sunlight
makes the world look crueler♪

654
00:39:00,781 --> 00:39:04,501
♪Wander through the echoes of regret♪

655
00:39:04,501 --> 00:39:08,541
♪Be forgiven and be sheltered♪

656
00:39:08,541 --> 00:39:12,581
♪After everything shatters,
hold my hand♪

657
00:39:12,581 --> 00:39:18,781
♪A flower reborn
will finally bloom forever♪
